   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">NO VIRTUAL CARDS<br />
DONT BELIEVE IN THEM<br />
Starting Cards:<br />
********************************************* <br />
Objective, Jabba’s Palace:  Audience Chamber, Jabba’s Palace:  Dungeon, Tatooine:  Great Pit of Carkoon, Fear is My Ally, Prepared Defenses, Secret Plans, All Wrapped Up, Imperial Decree.<br />
<br />
Strategy:<br />
**********************************************<br />
This deck revolves around the ability to create huge force swings in the game.  The bounty hunters in the deck can capture easily and using Elis Helrot, they can quickly get back to the dungeon to retrieve a ton of force when the captives have Bounty on them.    You can either get a couple of small worthless captives and then feed them to the Rancor or Sarlacc to retrieve more force and make the opponent lose some. <br />
<br />
Or, the way I like to do it, you can just run up with Dengar, put a Bounty on someone like Obi-Wan or Yoda if he&#39;s out, capture them quickly and then Elis Helrot to the Dungeon before you have a chance to take battle damage.  Throw Obi in the clink and retrieve tons of force.  Then feed him to the Rancor, retrieve more and make a take a huge chunk out of your opponent.<br />
<br />
Another thing to do in this deck is to put Galid in the AC and put Mosep around Jabba&#39;s Palace somewhere.  This can create super force drains right out of the opponent&#39;s reserve deck.  Get different aliens in the Palace and use Hutt Influence to prevent the enemy from donig anything about it.<br />
<br />
Get your bounty hunters into space and use them to get Imperial Decree working so that they can&#39;t force drain you into submission before you feed Jabba&#39;s pets.<br />
<br />
This deck has the potential to make huge swings in the game.  Sometimes you have to live on the edge of your reserve deck, but then all of a sudden you can turn the game right around on your opponent.<br />
